<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="212" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,524,1049,1113]" box="[151,302,1087,1113]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,295,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,705,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-192@12.[151,1436,705,1861]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 40–43. Ectrichodia crucifera Stål, 1872, male syntype deposited in NHRS, catalog number NHRS-GULI000000175; 40, dorsal view, scale bar 5 mm; 41, ventral view; 42, lateral view; 43, labels. Made available by the Swedish Museum of Natural History under Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International Public License, CC-BY 4.0, https://creativecommons. org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4673957" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4673957/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Figs. 40–43</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1158,2013]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,434,1158,1185]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Morphological remarks</emphasis>
. This species has a moderately large body size (
<quantity box="[967,1046,1158,1185]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
) for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1859" box="[1099,1195,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Rhiginia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1099,1195,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Rhiginia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Our material for this species was limited to images of the male 
<typeStatus box="[626,722,1195,1221]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stal" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[760,894,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Rhiginia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crucifera">
<emphasis box="[760,894,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">R. crucifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[910,1047,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,705,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-192@12.[151,1436,705,1861]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 40–43. Ectrichodia crucifera Stål, 1872, male syntype deposited in NHRS, catalog number NHRS-GULI000000175; 40, dorsal view, scale bar 5 mm; 41, ventral view; 42, lateral view; 43, labels. Made available by the Swedish Museum of Natural History under Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International Public License, CC-BY 4.0, https://creativecommons. org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4673957" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4673957/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Figs. 40–42</figureCitation>
), which matches the color patterns described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stal, C." box="[300,428,1230,1257]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" pagination="1 - 159" refId="ref23908" refString="Stal, C. (1872) Enumeratio Hemipterorum. Bidrag till en foreteckning ofver alla hittils kanda Hemiptera, jemte systematiska meddelanden. 2. Kongliga Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Handlingar, 10 (4), 1 - 159." type="journal article" year="1872">Stål (1872)</bibRefCitation>
: the body is dark brown-black, with the ocellar tubercle, two large spots between the eyes, and the anterior pronotal lobe (except at the margins and along the sulci) yellow-brown; the entire posterior pronotal lobe (including the longitudinal sulcus), base of the hemelytra, three irregular spots on or near the veins at the corium-membrane boundary, and the abdomen (except medially on syntergites I and II, sternite II except laterally, and pygophore) orange-red to sanguineous; the antennae and legs are brown. Previous descriptions of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stal" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[1302,1437,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Rhiginia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crucifera">
<emphasis box="[1302,1437,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">R. crucifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have not discussed color variation, and it remains unclear to what extent color patterns may deviate from the type specimen. The images reveal a relatively ovate head, convex frons, and moderately large ocelli that are separated by a distance subequal to the diameter of an ocellus and that occupy up to half of the ocellar tubercle in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[221,358,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,705,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-192@12.[151,1436,705,1861]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 40–43. Ectrichodia crucifera Stål, 1872, male syntype deposited in NHRS, catalog number NHRS-GULI000000175; 40, dorsal view, scale bar 5 mm; 41, ventral view; 42, lateral view; 43, labels. Made available by the Swedish Museum of Natural History under Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International Public License, CC-BY 4.0, https://creativecommons. org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4673957" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4673957/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Figs. 40, 42</figureCitation>
). While the clypeus is largely obscured by the antennae in lateral view of the 
<typeStatus box="[1222,1321,1519,1545]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">paratype</typeStatus>
, it may be more elevated than that seen in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[507,629,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Rhiginia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crudelis">
<emphasis box="[507,629,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">R. crudelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(a feature included in 
<bibRefCitation author="Stal, C." box="[883,1027,1554,1581]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" pagination="1 - 159" refId="ref23908" refString="Stal, C. (1872) Enumeratio Hemipterorum. Bidrag till en foreteckning ofver alla hittils kanda Hemiptera, jemte systematiska meddelanden. 2. Kongliga Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Handlingar, 10 (4), 1 - 159." type="journal article" year="1872">Stål’s [1872]</bibRefCitation>
differential diagnosis between these two species). The anterior pronotal lobe is approximately half the length of the posterior lobe, and the anterolateral protuberances of the anterior pronotal lobe are slightly prominent and rounded (best observed in 
<figureCitation box="[1262,1346,1627,1653]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,705,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-192@12.[151,1436,705,1861]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 40–43. Ectrichodia crucifera Stål, 1872, male syntype deposited in NHRS, catalog number NHRS-GULI000000175; 40, dorsal view, scale bar 5 mm; 41, ventral view; 42, lateral view; 43, labels. Made available by the Swedish Museum of Natural History under Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International Public License, CC-BY 4.0, https://creativecommons. org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4673957" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4673957/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
). While spread apart in the type, the hemelytra appear to reach the apex of the abdomen (or at least surpass the anterior margin of tergite VII) and have a subrectangular Cu+1A cell in the membrane (
<figureCitation box="[1028,1112,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,705,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-192@12.[151,1436,705,1861]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 40–43. Ectrichodia crucifera Stål, 1872, male syntype deposited in NHRS, catalog number NHRS-GULI000000175; 40, dorsal view, scale bar 5 mm; 41, ventral view; 42, lateral view; 43, labels. Made available by the Swedish Museum of Natural History under Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International Public License, CC-BY 4.0, https://creativecommons. org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4673957" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4673957/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
). The proximal margin of the Cu+1A membranal cell is about twice that of the M+Cu membranal cell (
<figureCitation box="[972,1056,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,705,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-192@12.[151,1436,705,1861]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 40–43. Ectrichodia crucifera Stål, 1872, male syntype deposited in NHRS, catalog number NHRS-GULI000000175; 40, dorsal view, scale bar 5 mm; 41, ventral view; 42, lateral view; 43, labels. Made available by the Swedish Museum of Natural History under Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International Public License, CC-BY 4.0, https://creativecommons. org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4673957" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4673957/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="213" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1158,2013]" lastBlockId="12.[151,1437,150,393]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="213" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1770,1796]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1872" box="[341,585,1771,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera" genus="Ectrichodia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crucifera">
<emphasis box="[341,585,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Ectrichodia crucifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on male (
<figureCitation box="[944,1082,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,705,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-192@12.[151,1436,705,1861]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 40–43. Ectrichodia crucifera Stål, 1872, male syntype deposited in NHRS, catalog number NHRS-GULI000000175; 40, dorsal view, scale bar 5 mm; 41, ventral view; 42, lateral view; 43, labels. Made available by the Swedish Museum of Natural History under Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International Public License, CC-BY 4.0, https://creativecommons. org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4673957" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4673957/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Figs. 40–43</figureCitation>
) and brachypterous (hemelytra extending to approximately the midportion of abdomen) female specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[1077,1166,1807,1833]" name="Mexico" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Stal, C." box="[1179,1306,1806,1833]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" pagination="1 - 159" refId="ref23908" refString="Stal, C. (1872) Enumeratio Hemipterorum. Bidrag till en foreteckning ofver alla hittils kanda Hemiptera, jemte systematiska meddelanden. 2. Kongliga Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Handlingar, 10 (4), 1 - 159." type="journal article" year="1872">Stål (1872)</bibRefCitation>
considered this species to be very close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[498,619,1843,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Rhiginia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crudelis">
<emphasis box="[498,619,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">E. crudelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while listing color patterns and two subtle structural traits to distinguish the two. 
<bibRefCitation author="Champion, G. C." box="[251,450,1879,1905]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" pagination="1 - 22" refId="ref22241" refString="Champion, G. C. (1899) [Printing sheets 27 - 28, containing pp. 211 - 226, pl. XIII]. In: Godman, F. D. &amp; Salvin, O. (Eds.), Biologia Centrali Americana. Insecta Rhynchota. Hemiptera-Heteroptera. Vol. II (1897 - 1901). Taylor &amp; Francis, London, pp. i - xvi + 1 - 416, pls. 1 - 22." type="book chapter" year="1899">Champion (1899)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1872" box="[587,722,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera" genus="Ectrichodia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crucifera">
<emphasis box="[587,722,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">E. crucifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[999,1121,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Rhiginia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crudelis">
<emphasis box="[999,1121,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">E. crudelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, describing it as a variation of the latter using one of the characteristics stated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stal, C." box="[765,892,1914,1941]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" pagination="1 - 159" refId="ref23908" refString="Stal, C. (1872) Enumeratio Hemipterorum. Bidrag till en foreteckning ofver alla hittils kanda Hemiptera, jemte systematiska meddelanden. 2. Kongliga Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Handlingar, 10 (4), 1 - 159." type="journal article" year="1872">Stål (1872)</bibRefCitation>
as distinctive of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1872" box="[1090,1226,1915,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera" genus="Ectrichodia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crucifera">
<emphasis box="[1090,1226,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">E. crucifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, i.e., the darkened longitudinal and transverse sulci of the pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[706,789,1951,1977]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–43" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,705,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-192@12.[151,1436,705,1861]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 40–43. Ectrichodia crucifera Stål, 1872, male syntype deposited in NHRS, catalog number NHRS-GULI000000175; 40, dorsal view, scale bar 5 mm; 41, ventral view; 42, lateral view; 43, labels. Made available by the Swedish Museum of Natural History under Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International Public License, CC-BY 4.0, https://creativecommons. org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4673957" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4673957/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Champion, G. C." box="[807,1004,1951,1977]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" pagination="1 - 22" refId="ref22241" refString="Champion, G. C. (1899) [Printing sheets 27 - 28, containing pp. 211 - 226, pl. XIII]. In: Godman, F. D. &amp; Salvin, O. (Eds.), Biologia Centrali Americana. Insecta Rhynchota. Hemiptera-Heteroptera. Vol. II (1897 - 1901). Taylor &amp; Francis, London, pp. i - xvi + 1 - 416, pls. 1 - 22." type="book chapter" year="1899">Champion (1899)</bibRefCitation>
did not include discussion of structural similarities to support this taxonomic act. Subsequent authors, however, have considered the species valid under the current combination, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stal" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[445,655,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Rhiginia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crucifera">
<emphasis box="[445,655,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">Rhiginia crucifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wygodzinsky, P." box="[673,899,151,177]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" pagination="1 - 102" refId="ref24198" refString="Wygodzinsky, P. (1949) Elenco sistematico de los reduviiformes americanos. Instituto de Medicina Regional de la Universidad Nacional de Tucuman, Monografia 1, 1 - 102." type="journal article" year="1949">Wygodzinsky 1949</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Maldonado Capriles, J." box="[915,1112,151,177]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" pagination="1 - 694" refId="ref23667" refString="Maldonado Capriles, J. (1990) Systematic catalogue of the Reduviidae of the world (Insecta: Heteroptera). Caribbean Journal of Science University of Puerto Rico, Special Edition, 1 - 694." type="book chapter" year="1990">Maldonado 1990</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dougherty, V." box="[1128,1318,150,177]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" pagination="173 - 225" refId="ref22383" refString="Dougherty, V. (1995) A review of the New World Ectrichodiinae genera (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 121, 173 - 225." type="journal article" year="1995">Dougherty 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Baena, M. &amp; Susin, J." pageId="12" pageNumber="213" pagination="113 - 119" refId="ref22009" refString="Baena, M. &amp; Susin, J. (2007) Rhiginia guentheri - a new species from Peru Heteroptera: Reduviidae: Ectrichodiinae). Mainzer Naturwissenschaftliches Archiv, Beiheft, 31, 113 - 119." type="journal article" year="2007">Baena &amp; Susín 2007</bibRefCitation>
). Almost all the aforementioned authors cite the geographical distribution of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stal" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[1167,1303,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Rhiginia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crucifera">
<emphasis box="[1167,1303,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">R. crucifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<collectingCountry box="[1344,1432,187,213]" name="Mexico" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, while 
<bibRefCitation author="Dougherty, V." box="[220,421,222,249]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" pagination="173 - 225" refId="ref22383" refString="Dougherty, V. (1995) A review of the New World Ectrichodiinae genera (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 121, 173 - 225." type="journal article" year="1995">Dougherty (1995)</bibRefCitation>
only listed 
<collectingCountry box="[551,669,223,249]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[679,801,223,249]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[855,947,223,249]" name="Panama" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">Panama</collectingCountry>
. It is evident that more specimen material is required to re-describe 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stal" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[408,541,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Rhiginia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crucifera">
<emphasis box="[408,541,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">R. crucifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in which we highlight the need for more documentation of structural characters, as well as color variation.
</paragraph>
